Ricardo Gutiérrez Mouat, Michael Palencia-Roth, Aníbal González, and Gonzalo Díaz-Migoyo offer English-speaking readers a new approach to García Márquez's work. Their poststructuralist readings focus on the peculiar sign-system, formal configuration, intradiscursivity, and unfolding representation in the novels One Hundred Years of Solitude, No One Writes to the Colonel, In Evil Hour, The Autumn of the Patriarch, and Chronicle of a Death Foretold and in several of the author's short stories. Also included as an appendix is a translation of García Márquez's Nobel Prize acceptance speech, "The Solitude of Latin America."  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aGarcia Marquez, Gabriel - Criticism and interpretation. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Caribbean & Latin American.2bisacsh1 aDíaz-Migoyo, Gonzalo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGarcia Márquez, Gabriel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGonzález, Aníbal, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGutiérrez Mouat, Ricardo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOrtega, Julio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPalencia-Roth, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780292767850423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780292767850/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK